    "The limitation of generalizability is more remarkable for expert-dependent processes of feature creation and knowledge-based feature selection, where decision-making is based on an expert's knowledge.",
    "Although such methods can create highly valuable data concerning the predicted object, the ideas described in the data composition cannot be applied to other cases because the defining sets of features are selected based on a particular problem or a researched object.",
    "This simply means that the success of feature engineering in a given case does not imply that the same methods will be used in another case.",
